<context>
Write a professional but approachable email to the user's team regarding a delay in the Q3 roadmap timeline.
</context>

<task>
Write an email informing the team that the Q3 roadmap is slipping by three weeks due to a vendor delay. The tone should be professional yet not overly corporate or stiff. Avoid blaming the vendor or any team members. Mention that there is a mitigation plan in place, but the details have not yet been finalized. Clearly communicate what aspects of the roadmap are changing and what will remain the same.
</task>

<constraints>
Maintain a balanced tone that is professional but approachable. Do not assign blame to the vendor or team members. Be transparent about the delay and the existence of a mitigation plan without providing incomplete details. Ensure clarity on changes versus unchanged elements of the roadmap.
</constraints>

<output_format>
An email addressed to the team with a clear subject line, opening greeting, body paragraphs covering the delay, mitigation plan, and roadmap changes, and a professional closing.
</output_format>